tasks.description:
Create an intelligent intent parser that extracts structured actions from casual natural language. This is the brain that lets non-technical users operate the exchange.

Create `src/admin-bot/orchestrator/src/intent-parser.ts`:

1. Define 15 intent categories matching all admin actions:
   ```typescript
   type Intent = 
     | { action: 'health_check' }
     | { action: 'list_instruments' }
     | { action: 'halt_instrument', instrument: string }
     | { action: 'resume_instrument', instrument: string }
     | { action: 'set_circuit_breaker', instrument: string, upper: number, lower: number }
     | { action: 'list_participants', status?: string }
     | { action: 'approve_kyc', participant_id: string }
     | { action: 'reject_kyc', participant_id: string, reason: string }
     | { action: 'suspend_participant', participant_id: string, reason: string }
     | { action: 'reinstate_participant', participant_id: string }
     | { action: 'view_margin_calls' }
     | { action: 'trigger_margin_calc', participant_id?: string }
     | { action: 'view_positions', participant_id?: string }
     | { action: 'trigger_settlement' }
     | { action: 'view_settlement_cycles' }
     | { action: 'view_alerts', severity?: string }
     | { action: 'resolve_alert', alert_id: string }
     | { action: 'file_sar', participant_id: string, reason: string }
     | { action: 'view_orderbook', instrument?: string }
     | { action: 'view_ticker', instrument?: string }
     | { action: 'bust_trade', trade_id: string, reason: string }
     | { action: 'mass_cancel' }
     | { action: 'view_inventory' }
     | { action: 'view_receipts', status?: string }
     | { action: 'view_deliveries' }
     | { action: 'view_risk_limits' }
     | { action: 'update_risk_limits', instrument: string, max_qty: number }
     | { action: 'generate_report', type: 'market_summary' | 'large_trader', date: string }
     | { action: 'view_fees' }
     | { action: 'create_ticket', title: string, description: string, category: string, priority: string }
     | { action: 'list_tickets', status?: string }
     | { action: 'update_ticket', id: string, status?: string }
     | { action: 'view_audit_trail', filters?: Record<string, string> }
     | { action: 'help', topic?: string }
     | { action: 'unknown', message: string }
   ```

2. Instrument name resolver:
   - 'wheat' | 'WHT' → 'WHT-HRW-2026M07-UB'
   - 'corn' | 'CRN' → 'CRN-YEL-2026M09-UB'
   - 'soybeans' | 'soy' | 'SBN' → 'SBN-NO2-2026M11-UB'
   - 'barley' | 'BRL' → 'BRL-MALT-2026M07-UB'
   - 'cashmere' | 'CSH' → 'CSH-RAW-2026M09-UB'
   - 'cattle' | 'livestock' | 'LVS' → 'LVS-CATTLE-2026M10-UB'
   - Fuzzy match: if no exact match, find closest

3. GPT-nano intent extraction (when OPENAI_API_KEY available):
   - System prompt with all intents + examples
   - Function calling to return structured Intent
   - Fallback to keyword parser if no API key

4. Keyword-based intent extraction (always available):
   - Pattern rules for each intent
   - Extract entity values (IDs, names, numbers) from message
   - Support conversational phrases: 'can you halt trading on wheat?', 'please show me the margin status', 'I need to suspend user xyz'

5. Confirmation prompts for dangerous actions:
   - halt_instrument, bust_trade, mass_cancel, suspend_participant, file_sar → return confirmation request
   - User must reply 'yes' / 'confirm' to execute
   - Store pending action in conversation state

Acceptance: Parser correctly extracts intents from 50+ natural language variations. Instrument aliases work. Dangerous actions require confirmation.
